  "chapter": {
    "number": 12,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Reproof of Ephraim, Judah, and Jacob"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2498
          },
          {
            "text": "chases the wind",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pursues the east wind all day long;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he multiplies lies and violence;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he makes a covenant with Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sends olive oil to Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD also brings a charge against Judah.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will punish Jacob",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2499
          },
          {
            "text": "according to his ways",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and repay him according to his deeds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the womb he grasped his brother’s heel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in his vigor he wrestled with God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yes, he struggled with the angel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2500
          },
          {
            "text": "and prevailed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he wept and sought His favor;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he found Him at Bethel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and spoke with Him there",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2501
          },
          {
            "text": "—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the LORD is the God of Hosts—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD is His name of renown.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you must return to your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "maintaining love and justice,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and always waiting on your God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A merchant loves to defraud",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with dishonest scales in his hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And Ephraim boasts: “How rich I have become!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have found wealth for myself.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In all my labors, they can find in me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no iniquity that is sinful.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But I am the LORD your God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "ever since the land of Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will again make you dwell in tents,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as in the days of the appointed feast.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I spoke through the prophets",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and multiplied their visions;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I gave parables through the prophets.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is there iniquity in Gilead?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "They will surely come to nothing.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do they sacrifice bulls in Gilgal?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, their altars will be heaps of stones",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "in the furrows of the field.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Jacob fled to the land of Aram",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2502
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel worked for a wife—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for a wife he tended sheep.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But by a prophet the LORD brought Israel out of Egypt,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and by a prophet he was preserved.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ephraim has provoked bitter anger,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so his Lord will leave his bloodguilt upon him",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and repay him for his contempt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2498,
